          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "64-GD-156",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9358
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Isotopically enriched gadolinium",
                "metal evaporated onto carbon backings was used to form",
                "targets   of 100-150 mug/cm**2 thickness.",
                "The purity of the enriched materials is-",
                "Gd-156 93.58%, Gd-153 less than 0.05%,",
                "Gd-154 0.13%, Gd-155 1.99%, Gd-157 2.57%,",
                "Gd-158 1.27%, Gd-159 0.46%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "64-GD-158(HE3,EL)64-GD-158,,DA,,RTH",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "64-GD-158(HE3,EL)64-GD-158,,DA,,RTH",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "64-GD-158(HE3,EL)64-GD-158",
                        "target": "64-GD-158",
                        "projectile": "HE3",
                        "process": "EL",
                        "product": "64-GD-158",
                        "quantity": ",DA,,RTH",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA,,RTH"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The experimental cross sections divided by the",
                "Rutherford cross section were found to be  1.0 +- 0.1",
                "and 0.55 +- 0.05 at 60. and 90. degr., respectively.",
                "Theoretical calculations of these ratios with the same",
                "optical-model parameters which were used for the DWBA",
                "calculations of the (3He,alpha) cross sections give",
                "values of 0.92 and 0.50 in good agreement with the",
                "measured values."
              ]
            }
          ],
